OL,4,Con sleeping pupils at private school
OL,6,FHe denied three counts of attempted
OL,7,Fmurder - claiming he had been
OL,8,Fsleepwalking - but was found guilty by
OL,9,Fa jury on all three counts following a
OL,10,F10-week trial.
OL,12,FDuring a sentencing hearing at Exeter
OL,13,FCrown Court on 18 October, the 17-year-
OL,14,Fold was sentenced to life in prison
OL,15,Fwith a minimum term of 12 years.
OL,17,FThe judge, Mrs Justice Cutts, told the
OL,18,Fboy: "You knew the difference between
OL,19,Fright and wrong and you intended to
OL,20,Fkill those boys.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/16
