OL,3,CBoy jailed for life for hammer attack
OL,4,Con sleeping pupils at private school
OL,6,F"They were extremely vulnerable,
OL,7,Fasleep in their beds at school. They
OL,8,Fcouldn't defend themselves in any way."
OL,10,FThe judge said the teenager kept the
OL,11,Fhammers in what he called his "weapons
OL,12,Fdrawer", adding: "I am sure you
OL,13,Fintended to use them as weapons
OL,14,Fagainst one or more boys at school."
OL,16,FMrs Justice Cutts described the boy as
OL,17,Fposing a "high level" of danger to the
OL,18,Fpublic, saying there is a
OL,19,F"significant" risk he could behave in
OL,20,Fthe same way again.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/16
