OL,6,FThe court heard the teenager, who was
OL,7,F16 at the time, armed himself with
OL,8,Fthree claw hammers and waited for his
OL,9,Fdorm-mates to be asleep before
OL,10,Flaunching his attack.
OL,12,FThe two pupils were asleep in cabin-
OL,13,Fstyle beds in one of the co-
OL,14,Feducational school's boarding houses
OL,15,Fwhen the offender climbed up and
OL,16,Fattacked them shortly before 1am.
OL,18,FTheir housemaster, Henry Roffe-
OL,19,FSilvester, who was asleep in his room,
OL,20,Fwas awoken by noises coming from the
OL,21,Fboarding house and went to investigate.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/16
