OL,6,FThe court heard how in the months
OL,7,Fbefore the attack, the offender
OL,8,Fresearched serial killers and asked
OL,9,Fquestions such as, "what happens if
OL,10,Fyou hit someone on the head with a
OL,11,Fhammer?" and whether young people went
OL,12,Fto prison.
OL,14,FMr Dawes told the jury that an
OL,15,Fexamination of the offender's iPad
OL,16,Frevealed he had been listening to
OL,17,Fmusic moments before launching the
OL,18,Fassaults, which proved that he had not
OL,19,Ffallen asleep but had instead been
OL,20,Ffully conscious.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/16
